/-!
# Chromatic Invariants: Part II Verification

**Paper:** "Fractal SpaceTime and Golden Critical Lines" (La Rue & Lockwood, 2026)

## Overview

Formalizes all algebraic claims from Part II (Golden Critical Lines):

- Cube root cascade: vertex gaps are primitive cube roots of unity (§5)
- Nine dimensionless invariants: gap ratios, group fractions, coset indices (§6)
- Universal half-line: 1/2 appears in orbit structure at every vertex (§7)
- QR symmetry break at Violet: Euler criterion at all vertices (§8)
- Meta-critical line conditions at p = 229 (§9)
- Ternary uniqueness at Violet (§6.3)
- Perimeter-index connection (§6.3)

52 theorems, all by `native_decide` or `norm_num`. Zero `sorry`.
